Polyphenols, in particular proanthocyanidin polymers are a large groups of phytochemicals that can be extracted from plants such as tea, coffee, wine, cocoa, grains, legumes, fruits and berries 
 (
  Chen et al., 2012)
 . Several findings have confirmed that there is a positive correlation between the antioxidant such as polyphenols present and the α-glucosidase and α-amylase inhibition (
 Cai et al., 2004; 
 Peng et al., 2010; 
 Abeysekera, Premakumara & Ratnasooriya, 2013; 
 Chandrasekharan & Bentota, 2013). SW, DWE and PWE had high contents of PC and TPC, which can be correlated with the observed better anti-diabetic activities (
